joyment of Everquest in griefing others (well at least most pks, there are some out there who actually love pvp and are good at it, few LV fall into this category)  PVP = the ability to fight between PC characters.  This is to add realism to the game.  When a dispute arises, instead of saying &quot;hey we are on a care bear server and have PNP rules let's share&quot; we can instead, if we want, say &quot;get the fuck out or let's fight&quot;.  PVP means we have the option and ability to attack each other, that does not translate into portal gank, out number, exploit any way you can to grief a player for his loot to sell on player auctions to support your online porn habits.  Have we all understood this lesson?  RZ is not a pk server, albeit there are pks here and they get shit on.  Live with it =) <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.ascendingdawn.com/cgi-bin/profile.pl?page=inspect&amp;id=204target=top">Slivur</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
